  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "The original commit for `hack/verify-flags/known-flags.txt` claims that the purpose is for preventing flags that have `_` in the flag name. It claims that this list is used to speed up the search so that it is not obtrusive as a pre-commit hook. \r\n\r\nDoes anyone actually use the pre-commit hooks anymore? When I joined the project, these already took so long that I almost immediately turned them off.\r\n\r\nCan we move flag verification off of relying on known-flags.txt and no longer have to edit that file every time we add/remove a flag?\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/test-infra-reviewers what do y'all think of this?",
